# 1. 進む先は

Kanade: Here's your tea.
Mafuyu's Father: Ah, thank you. I'm always grateful for your hospitality.
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu's Father: So, how have you been lately? I hope you're feeling well.
Mafuyu: Yes, I've been fine...
Mafuyu's Father: Okay, that's good to hear.
Mafuyu's Father: Oh, that reminds me. I bought some shortcake from that bakery by the station.
Mafuyu's Father: You like these quite a lot if I recall. Please have some with Ms. Yoisaki later.
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu's Father: Hm?
Mafuyu: Nothing. Thank you...
Mafuyu's Father: It's okay for you to tell me whatever it is that's on your mind, Mafuyu...
Mafuyu: Huh...?
Mafuyu's Father: But you also don't have to if you don't want to tell me.
Mafuyu's Father: However, I'm here because I want to know how you're feeling. I'm here to listen.
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: So...
Mafuyu's Father: Hm? Yes?
Mafuyu: I don't actually like this cake.
Mafuyu's Father: I see...
Mafuyu's Father: I'm sorry for misunderstanding. Then, can you tell me what you do like?
Mafuyu: I don't know...
Mafuyu's Father: What?
Mafuyu: I haven't been able to taste anything for a while now...
Mafuyu: Everything I eat... It's all the same to me...
Mafuyu's Father: You can't taste anything...?!
Mafuyu's Father: I see... Since when exactly?
Mafuyu's Father: If possible, could you tell me?
Mafuyu: Since...
Kanade: (Mafuyu seems more comfortable talking compared to before...)
Kanade: (And her dad's making an effort to understand what's going on with her. Thank goodness...)
Kanade: (I hope things start moving in a positive direction...)
Mafuyu's Father: Then, I'll be back again next week.
Mafuyu's Father: See you then, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: *Nod* See you then...
Kanade: Are you okay, Mafuyu...?
Mafuyu: I'm fine...
Mafuyu: But I'm a little tired... I'm going to rest for a bit.
Kanade: Okay. Then, I'll be working in my room.
Mafuyu: Okay...
Kanade: Huh? A call? Who could it be...?
Kanade: Hello? This is Yoisaki.
Kanade's Grandmother: <Kanade? It's your grandmother. Are you free to talk now?>
Kanade: Oh, Grandma...? Yes, now's okay.
Kanade: Is there a reason you called?
Kanade's Grandmother: <I was wondering how you've been doing, Kanade. Is everything okay?>
Kanade: Yes, I'm okay. Mafuyu... My friend's also doing well.
Kanade: And thanks to Ms. Mochizuki, I've been eating much more regularly. Also, my room's much cleaner now.
Kanade's Grandmother: <Oh, that's wonderful to hear...! I'll need to thank Honami again the next chance I get.>
Kanade's Grandmother: <By the way, Kanade, I heard that you went to your school's opening ceremony...>
Kanade: Oh, um... Yes, I did.
Kanade's Grandmother: <So, how was it? Were there changes or anything bothering you?>
Kanade: No, there's nothing in particular... I've been keeping up with my studies as usual.
Kanade: Dad also seems fine. Not much has changed...
Kanade's Grandmother: <I see...>
Kanade's Grandmother: <By the way, Kanade, have you been thinking about your future at all?>
Kanade: Huh?
Kanade's Grandmother: <I know that's difficult to do considering your father's condition...>
Kanade's Grandmother: <But I believe it's about time for you to start thinking more seriously about your own future.>
Kanade: My future...?
Kanade's Grandmother: <Yes. For starters, what are you going to do after you graduate? You need to begin planning for that.>
Kanade's Grandmother: <That's why I'd like to hear what you think, Kanade. What would you like to do...?>
Kanade: What would I like to do...?
Kanade: ...
Kanade's Grandmother: <I'm sorry. I know I'm throwing a tough question at you...>
Kanade's Grandmother: <But I hope you'll give it some thought when you get a chance... This is your future we're talking about.>
Kanade's Grandmother: <And I'll support you on whatever endeavors you decide to embark on...>
Kanade: Okay...
Kanade: I'll think about it.
Kanade's Grandmother: <Thank you. Then, take care...>
Kanade: Okay. Bye Grandma.
Kanade: ...
Kanade: My future...
